122Kg 11:13 Queen Athaliah heard the noise being made by the guards and the people, so she hurried to the Temple, where the crowd had gathered. 
122Kg 11:14 There she saw the new king standing by the column at the entrance of the Temple, as was the custom. He was surrounded by the officers and the trumpeters, and the people were all shouting joyfully and blowing trumpets. Athaliah tore her clothes in distress and shouted, "Treason! Treason!" 
122Kg 11:15 Jehoiada did not want Athaliah killed in the Temple area, so he ordered the army officers�� "Take her out between the rows of guards, and kill anyone who tries to rescue her." 
122Kg 11:16 They seized her, took her to the palace, and there at the Horse Gate they killed her. 
