122Kg 12:12 the masons, and the stone cutters, buy the timber and the stones used in the repairs, and pay all other necessary expenses. 
122Kg 12:13 None of the money, however, was used to pay for making silver cups, bowls, trumpets, or tools for tending the lamps, or any other article of silver or of gold. 
