131Ch 1:10 (Cush had a son named Nimrod, who became the world's first great conqueror.) 
131Ch 1:11 The descendants of Egypt were the people of Lydia, Anam, Lehab, Naphtuh, 
131Ch 1:12 Pathrus, Casluh, and of Crete (from whom the Philistines were descended). 
131Ch 1:13 Canaan's sons - Sidon, the oldest, and Heth - were the ancestors of the peoples who bear their names. 
131Ch 1:14 Canaan was also the ancestor of the Jebusites, the Amorites, Girgashites, 
131Ch 1:15 Hivites, Arkites, Sinites, 
131Ch 1:16 Arvadites, Zemarites, and Hamathites. 
131Ch 1:17 Shem's sons - Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, Aram, Uz, Hul, Gether, and Meshek - were the ancestors of the peoples who bear their names. 
131Ch 1:18 Arpachshad was the father of Shelah, who was the father of Eber. 
131Ch 1:19 Eber had two sons; one was named Peleg, because during his time the people of the world were divided, and the other was named Joktan. 
131Ch 1:20 The descendants of Joktan were the people of Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, 
131Ch 1:21 Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, 
131Ch 1:22 Ebal, Abimael, Sheba, 
131Ch 1:23 Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab. 
131Ch 1:24 The family line from Shem to Abram is as follows�� Shem, Arpachshad, Shelah, 
131Ch 1:25 Eber, Peleg, Reu, 
131Ch 1:26 Serug, Nahor, Terah, 
131Ch 1:27 and Abram (also known as Abraham). 
131Ch 1:28 Abraham had two sons, Isaac and Ishmael. 
131Ch 1:29 The sons of Ishmael became the heads of twelve tribes�� Nebaioth (from the name of Ishmael's oldest son), Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam, 
131Ch 1:30 Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema, 
131Ch 1:31 Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. 
131Ch 1:32 Abraham had a concubine named Keturah, who bore him six sons�� Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah. Jokshan had two sons�� Sheba and Dedan. 
131Ch 1:33 Midian had five sons�� Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah. 
131Ch 1:34 Abraham's son Isaac had two sons, Esau and Jacob. 
131Ch 1:35 Esau's sons were Eliphaz, Reuel, Jeush, Jalam, and Korah. 
131Ch 1:36 Eliphaz became the ancestor of the following tribes�� Teman, Omar, Zephi, Gatam, Kenaz, Timna, and Amalek. 
131Ch 1:37 And Reuel became the ancestor of the tribes of Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. 
131Ch 1:38 The original inhabitants of Edom were descended from the following sons of Seir�� Lotan, who was the ancestor of the clans of Hori and Homam. (Lotan had a sister named Timna.) 
131Ch 1:39 Shobal, who was the ancestor of the clans of Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shephi, and Onam. 
131Ch 1:40 Zibeon, who had two sons, Aiah and Anah. 
131Ch 1:41 Anah was the father of Dishon, and Dishon was the ancestor of the clans of Hamran, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran. 
131Ch 1:42 Ezer, who was the ancestor of the clans of Bilhan, Zaavan, and Jaakan. Dishan, who was the ancestor of the clans of Uz and Aran. 
131Ch 1:43 The following kings ruled the land of Edom one after the other, in the time before there were any kings in Israel�� 
131Ch 1:44 Bela son of Beor from Dinhabah,
131Ch 1:45 Jobab son of Zerah from Bozrah,
131Ch 1:46 Husham from the region of Teman,
131Ch 1:47 Hadad son of Bedad from Avith (he defeated the Midianites in a battle in the country of Moab),
131Ch 1:48 Samlah from Masrekah,
131Ch 1:49 Shaul from Rehoboth-on-the-River, Baal Hanan son of Achbor, Hadad from Pau (his wife was Mehetabel, 
131Ch 1:50 the daughter of Matred and granddaughter of Mezahab) 
131Ch 1:51 The people of Edom were divided into the following tribes�� Timna, Alvah, Jetheth, 
131Ch 1:52 Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon, 
131Ch 1:53 Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar, 
131Ch 1:54 Magdiel, and Iram. 
131Ch 2:1 Jacob had twelve sons�� Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Zebulun, 
131Ch 2:2 Dan, Joseph, Benjamin, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher. 
131Ch 2:3 Judah had five sons in all. By his wife Bathshua, a Canaanite, he had three sons�� Er, Onan, and Shelah. His oldest son, Er, was so evil that the LORD killed him. 
131Ch 2:4 By his daughter-in-law Tamar, Judah had two more sons, Perez and Zerah. 
131Ch 2:5 Perez had two sons, Hezron and Hamul. 
131Ch 2:6 His brother Zerah had five sons�� Zimri, Ethan, Heman, Calcol, and Darda. 
131Ch 2:7 Achan son of Carmi, one of Zerah's descendants, brought disaster on the people of Israel by keeping loot that had been devoted to God. 
131Ch 2:8 Ethan had one son, Azariah. 
131Ch 2:9 Hezron had three sons�� Jerahmeel, Ram, and Caleb. 
131Ch 2:10 The family line from Ram to Jesse is as follows�� Ram, Amminadab, Nahshon (a prominent man of the tribe of Judah), 
131Ch 2:11 Salmon, Boaz, 
131Ch 2:12 Obed, and Jesse. 
131Ch 2:13 Jesse had seven sons. In order of age they were�� Eliab, Abinadab, Shammah, 
131Ch 2:14 Nethanel, Raddai, 
131Ch 2:15 Ozem, and David. 
131Ch 2:16 He also had two daughters, Zeruiah and Abigail. Jesse's daughter Zeruiah had three sons�� Abishai, Joab, and Asahel. 
131Ch 2:17 His other daughter Abigail married Jether, a descendant of Ishmael, and they had a son named Amasa. 
131Ch 2:18 Hezron's son Caleb married Azubah and had a daughter named Jerioth. She had three sons�� Jesher, Shobab, and Ardon. 
131Ch 2:19 After the death of Azubah, Caleb married Ephrath, and they had a son named Hur. 
131Ch 2:20 Hur's son was Uri, and his grandson was Bezalel. 
131Ch 2:21 When Hezron was sixty years old, he married Machir's daughter, the sister of Gilead. They had a son named Segub, 
131Ch 2:22 and Segub had a son named Jair. Jair ruled twenty-three cities in the territory of Gilead. 
131Ch 2:23 But the kingdoms of Geshur and Aram conquered sixty towns there, including the villages of Jair and Kenath, and the towns nearby. All the people who lived there were descendants of Machir, the father of Gilead. 
131Ch 2:24 After Hezron died, his son Caleb married Ephrath, his father's widow. They had a son named Ashhur, who founded the town of Tekoa. 
131Ch 2:25 Jerahmeel, the oldest son of Hezron, had five sons�� Ram, the oldest, Bunah, Oren, Ozem, and Ahijah. 
131Ch 2:26 Ram had three sons�� Maaz, Jamin, and Eker. 
131Ch 2:27 Jerahmeel had another wife, a woman named Atarah, and they had a son, Onam. 
131Ch 2:28 Onam had two sons, Shammai and Jada, and Shammai also had two sons, Nadab and Abishur. 
131Ch 2:29 Abishur married a woman named Abihail, and they had two sons, Ahban and Molid. 
131Ch 2:30 Abishur's brother Nadab had two sons, Seled and Appaim, but Seled died without having any sons. 
131Ch 2:31 Appaim was the father of Ishi, Ishi was the father of Sheshan, and Sheshan the father of Ahlai. 
131Ch 2:32 Jada, the brother of Shammai, had two sons, Jether and Jonathan, but Jether died without having any sons. 
131Ch 2:33 Jonathan had two sons, Peleth and Zaza. All these were descendants of Jerahmeel. 
131Ch 2:34 Sheshan had no sons, only daughters. He had an Egyptian servant named Jarha, 
131Ch 2:35 to whom he gave one of his daughters in marriage. They had a son named Attai. 
131Ch 2:36 The family line from Attai to Elishama is as follows�� Attai, Nathan, Zabad, 
131Ch 2:37 Ephlal, Obed, 
131Ch 2:38 Jehu, Azariah, 
131Ch 2:39 Helez, Eleasah, 
131Ch 2:40 Sismai, Shallum, 
131Ch 2:41 Jekamiah, and Elishama. 
131Ch 2:42 The oldest son of Caleb, Jerahmeel's brother, was named Mesha. Mesha was the father of Ziph, who was the father of Mareshah, who was the father of Hebron. 
131Ch 2:43 Hebron had four sons�� Korah, Tappuah, Rekem, and Shema. 
131Ch 2:44 Shema was the father of Raham and the grandfather of Jorkeam. Rekem, Shema's brother, was the father of Shammai, 
131Ch 2:45 who was the father of Maon, who was the father of Bethzur. 
131Ch 2:46 Caleb had a concubine named Ephah, and by her he had three more sons�� Haran, Moza, and Gazez. Haran also had a son named Gazez. 
131Ch 2:47 (A man named Jahdai had six sons�� Regem, Jotham, Geshan, Pelet, Ephah, and Shaaph.) 
131Ch 2:48 Caleb had another concubine, Maacah, who bore him two sons, Sheber and Tirhanah. 
131Ch 2:49 Later she had two more sons�� Shaaph, who founded the town of Madmannah; and Shevah, who founded the towns of Machbenah and Gibea. In addition, Caleb had a daughter named Achsah. 
131Ch 2:50 The following are also descendants of Caleb. Hur was the oldest son of Caleb and his wife Ephrath. Hur's son Shobal founded Kiriath Jearim, 
131Ch 2:51 his second son Salma founded Bethlehem, and his third son Hareph founded Bethgader. 
131Ch 2:52 Shobal, the founder of Kiriath Jearim, was the ancestor of the people of Haroeh, of half the inhabitants of Menuhoth, 
131Ch 2:53 and of the following clans that lived in Kiriath Jearim�� the Ithrites, Puthites, Shumathites, and Mishraites. (The people of the cities of Zorah and Eshtaol were members of these clans.) 
131Ch 2:54 Salma, the founder of Bethlehem, was the ancestor of the people of Netophath, of Atroth Beth Joab, and of the Zorites, who were one of the two clans in Manahath. 
131Ch 2:55 (The following clans of experts in writing and copying documents lived in the town of Jabez�� the Tirathites, Shimeathites, and Sucathites. They were Kenites who had intermarried with the Rechabites.) 
131Ch 3:1 The following, in order of age, are David's sons who were born while he was in Hebron��
131Ch 3:2 Amnon, whose mother was Ahinoam from Jezreel. Daniel, whose mother was Abigail from Carmel. Absalom, whose mother was Maacah, daughter of King Talmai of Geshur.
131Ch 3:3 Adonijah, whose mother was Haggith. Shephatiah, whose mother was Abital. Ithream, whose mother was Eglah 
131Ch 3:4 All six were born in Hebron during the seven and a half years that David ruled there. In Jerusalem he ruled as king for thirty-three years, 
131Ch 3:5 and many sons were born to him there. His wife Bathsheba, daughter of Ammiel, bore him four sons�� Shimea, Shobab, Nathan, and Solomon. 
131Ch 3:6 He had nine other sons�� Ibhar, Elishua, Elpelet, 
131Ch 3:7 Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia, 
131Ch 3:8 Elishama, Eliada, and Eliphelet. 
131Ch 3:9 In addition to all these sons, David had sons by his concubines. He also had a daughter, Tamar. 
131Ch 3:10 This is the line of King Solomon's descendants from father to son�� Solomon, Rehoboam, Abijah, Asa, Jehoshaphat, 
131Ch 3:11 Jehoram, Ahaziah, Joash, 
131Ch 3:12 Amaziah, Uzziah, Jotham, 
131Ch 3:13 Ahaz, Hezekiah, Manasseh, 
131Ch 3:14 Amon, and Josiah. 
131Ch 3:15 Josiah had four sons�� Johanan, Jehoiakim, Zedekiah, and Joahaz. 
131Ch 3:16 Jehoiakim had two sons�� Jehoiachin and Zedekiah. 
131Ch 3:17 These are the descendants of King Jehoiachin, who was taken prisoner by the Babylonians. Jehoiachin had seven sons�� Shealtiel, 
131Ch 3:18 Malchiram, Pedaiah, Shenazzar, Jekamiah, Hoshama, and Nedabiah. 
131Ch 3:19 Pedaiah had two sons, Zerubbabel and Shimei. Zerubbabel was the father of two sons, Meshullam and Hananiah, and one daughter, Shelomith. 
131Ch 3:20 He had five other sons�� Hashubah, Ohel, Berechiah, Hasadiah, and Jushab Hesed. 
131Ch 3:21 Hananiah had two sons, Pelatiah and Jeshaiah. Jeshaiah was the father of Rephaiah, who was the father of Arnan, the father of Obadiah, the father of Shecaniah. 
131Ch 3:22 Shecaniah had one son, Shemaiah, and five grandsons�� Hattush, Igal, Bariah, Neariah, and Shaphat. 
131Ch 3:23 Neariah had three sons�� Elioenai, Hizkiah, and Azrikam. 
131Ch 3:24 Elioenai had seven sons�� Hodaviah, Eliashib, Pelaiah, Akkub, Johanan, Delaiah, and Anani. 
131Ch 4:1 These are some of the descendants of Judah�� Perez, Hezron, Carmi, Hur, and Shobal. 
131Ch 4:2 Shobal was the father of Reaiah, who was the father of Jahath, the father of Ahumai and Lahad, the ancestors of the people who lived in Zorah. 
131Ch 4:3 Hur was the oldest son of his father Caleb's wife Ephrath, and his descendants founded the city of Bethlehem. Hur had three sons�� Etam, Penuel, and Ezer. 
131Ch 4:4 Etam had three sons�� Jezreel, Ishma, and Idbash, and one daughter, Hazzelelponi. Penuel founded the city of Gedor, and Ezer founded Hushah. 
131Ch 4:5 Ashhur, who founded the town of Tekoa, had two wives, Helah and Naarah. 
131Ch 4:6 He and Naarah had four sons�� Ahuzzam, Hepher, Temeni, and Haahashtari. 
131Ch 4:7 Ashhur and Helah had three sons�� Zereth, Izhar, and Ethnan. 
131Ch 4:8 Koz was the father of Anub and Zobebah, and the ancestor of the clans descended from Aharhel son of Harum. 
131Ch 4:9 There was a man named Jabez, who was the most respected member of his family. His mother had given him the name Jabez, because his birth had been very painful. 
131Ch 4:10 But Jabez prayed to the God of Israel, "Bless me, God, and give me much land. Be with me and keep me from anything evil that might cause me pain." And God gave him what he prayed for. 
131Ch 4:11 Caleb, the brother of Shuhah, had a son, Mehir. Mehir was the father of Eshton, 
131Ch 4:12 who had three sons�� Bethrapha, Paseah, and Tehinnah. Tehinnah was the founder of the city of Nahash. The descendants of these men lived in Recah. 
131Ch 4:13 Kenaz had two sons, Othniel and Seraiah. Othniel also had two sons, Hathath and Meonothai. 
131Ch 4:14 Meonothai was the father of Ophrah. Seraiah was the father of Joab, the founder of Handcraft Valley, where all the people were skilled workers. 
131Ch 4:15 Caleb son of Jephunneh had three sons�� Iru, Elah, and Naam. And Elah was the father of Kenaz. 
131Ch 4:16 Jehallelel had four sons�� Ziph, Ziphah, Tiria, and Asarel. 
131Ch 4:17 Ezrah had four sons�� Jether, Mered, Epher, and Jalon. Mered married Bithiah, a daughter of the king of Egypt, and they had a daughter, Miriam, and two sons, Shammai and Ishbah.
131Ch 4:18 Ishbah founded the town of Eshtemoa. Mered also married a woman from the tribe of Judah, and they had three sons�� Jered, who founded the town of Gedor; Heber, founder of the town of Soco; and Jekuthiel, founder of the town of Zanoah. 
131Ch 4:19 Hodiah married the sister of Naham. Their descendants founded the clan of Garm, which lived in the town of Keilah, and the clan of Maacath, which lived in the town of Eshtemoa. 
131Ch 4:20 Shimon had four sons�� Amnon, Rinnah, Benhanan, and Tilon. Ishi had two sons�� Zoheth and Benzoheth. 
131Ch 4:21 Shelah was one of Judah's sons. His descendants included Er, who founded the town of Lecah; Laadah, founder of the town of Mareshah; the clan of linen weavers, who lived in the town of Beth Ashbea; 
131Ch 4:22 Jokim and the people who lived in the town of Cozeba; and Joash and Saraph, who married Moabite women and then settled in Bethlehem. (These traditions are very old.) 
131Ch 4:23 They were potters in the service of the king and lived in the towns of Netaim and Gederah. 
131Ch 4:24 Simeon had five sons�� Nemuel, Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, and Shaul. 
131Ch 4:25 Shaul's son was Shallum, his grandson was Mibsam, and his great-grandson was Mishma. 
131Ch 4:26 Then from Mishma the line descended through Hammuel, Zaccur, and Shimei. 
131Ch 4:27 Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters, but his relatives had fewer children, and the tribe of Simeon did not grow as much as the tribe of Judah did. 
131Ch 4:28 Down to the time of King David the descendants of Simeon lived in the following towns�� Beersheba, Moladah, Hazarshual, 
131Ch 4:29 Bilhah, Ezem, Tolad, 
131Ch 4:30 Bethuel, Hormah, Ziklag, 
131Ch 4:31 Beth Marcaboth, Hazarsusim, Bethbiri, and Shaaraim. 
131Ch 4:32 They also lived in five other places�� Etam, Ain, Rimmon, Tochen, and Ashan, 
131Ch 4:33 and the surrounding villages, as far southwest as the town of Baalath. These are the records which they kept of their families and of the places where they lived. 
131Ch 4:34 The following men were the heads of their clans��
131Ch 4:35 Meshobab, Jamlech, Joshah son of Amaziah, Joel, Jehu (the son of Joshibiah, the son of Seraiah, the son of Asiel),
131Ch 4:36 Elioenai, Jaakobah, Jeshohaiah, Asaiah, Adiel, Jesimiel, Benaiah, 
131Ch 4:37 Ziza (the son of Shiphi, the son of Allon, a descendant of Jedaiah, Shimri, and Shemaiah). 
131Ch 4:38 Because their families continued to grow,
131Ch 4:39 they spread out westward almost to Gerar and pastured their sheep on the eastern side of the valley in which that city is located. 
131Ch 4:40 They found plenty of fertile pasture lands there in a stretch of open country that was quiet and peaceful. The people who had lived there before were Hamites. 
131Ch 4:41 In the time of King Hezekiah of Judah, the men named above went to Gerar and destroyed the tents and huts of the people who lived there. They drove the people out and settled there permanently because there was plenty of pasture for their sheep. 
131Ch 4:42 Five hundred other members of the tribe of Simeon went east to Edom. They were led by the sons of Ishi�� Pelatiah, Neariah, Rephaiah, and Uzziel. 
131Ch 4:43 There they killed the surviving Amalekites, and they have lived there ever since. 
131Ch 5:1 These are the descendants of Reuben, the oldest of Jacob's sons. (Because he had sex with one of his father's concubines, he lost the rights belonging to the first-born son, and those rights were given to Joseph. 
131Ch 5:2 It was the tribe of Judah, however, that became the strongest and provided a ruler for all the tribes.) 
131Ch 5:3 Reuben, the oldest of Jacob's sons, had four sons�� Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi. 
131Ch 5:4 These are the descendants of Joel from generation to generation��
131Ch 5:5 Shemaiah, Gog, Shimei, Micah, Reaiah, Baal, and Beerah. 
131Ch 5:6 The Assyrian emperor, Tiglath Pileser, captured Beerah, a leader of the tribe, and deported him. 
131Ch 5:7 The family records list the following clan leaders in the tribe of Reuben�� Jeiel, Zechariah, 
131Ch 5:8 and Bela, the son of Azaz and grandson of Shema, of the clan of Joel. This clan lived in Aroer and in the territory from there north to Nebo and Baal Meon. 
131Ch 5:9 They had large herds in the land of Gilead, and so they occupied the land as far east as the desert that stretches all the way to the Euphrates River. 
131Ch 5:10 In the time of King Saul the tribe of Reuben attacked the Hagrites, killed them in battle, and occupied their land in the eastern part of Gilead. 
131Ch 5:11 The tribe of Gad lived to the north of Reuben in the land of Bashan as far east as Salecah. 
131Ch 5:12 Joel was the founder of the leading clan, and Shapham of the second most important clan. Janai and Shaphat were founders of other clans in Bashan. 
131Ch 5:13 The other members of the tribe belonged to the following seven clans�� Michael, Meshullam, Sheba, Jorai, Jacan, Zia, and Eber. 
131Ch 5:14 They were descendants of Abihail son of Huri, whose ancestors were traced back as follows�� Abihail, Huri, Jaroah, Gilead, Michael, Jeshishai, Jahdo, Buz. 
131Ch 5:15 Ahi, the son of Abdiel and grandson of Guni, was head of these clans. 
131Ch 5:16 They lived in the territory of Bashan and Gilead, in the towns there and all over the pasture lands of Sharon. 
131Ch 5:17 (These records were compiled in the days of King Jotham of Judah and King Jeroboam II of Israel.) 
131Ch 5:18 In the tribes of Reuben, Gad, and East Manasseh there were 44,760 soldiers, well-trained in the use of shields, swords, and bows. 
131Ch 5:19 They went to war against the Hagrite tribes of Jetur, Naphish, and Nodab. 
131Ch 5:20 They put their trust in God and prayed to him for help, and God answered their prayers and made them victorious over the Hagrites and their allies. 
131Ch 5:21 They captured from the enemy 50,000 camels, 250,000 sheep, and 2,000 donkeys, and took 100,000 prisoners of war. 
131Ch 5:22 They killed many of the enemy, because the war was God's will. And they went on living in that territory until the exile. 
131Ch 5:23 The people of East Manasseh settled in the territory of Bashan as far north as Baal Hermon, Senir, and Mount Hermon, and their population increased greatly. 
131Ch 5:24 The following were the heads of their clans�� Epher, Ishi, Eliel, Azriel, Jeremiah, Hodaviah, and Jahdiel. They were all outstanding soldiers, well-known leaders of their clans. 
131Ch 5:25 But the people were unfaithful to the God of their ancestors and deserted him to worship the gods of the nations whom God had driven out of the land. 
131Ch 5:26 So God caused Emperor Pul of Assyria (also known as Tiglath Pileser) to invade their country. He deported the tribes of Reuben, Gad, and East Manasseh and settled them permanently in Halah, Habor, and Hara, and by the Gozan River. 
